    <section class="methodology card">
      <h2>Our Methodology</h2>
      <p>Ranking Bitcoin ETFs requires a specialized approach, as the underlying asset is identical across spot funds. Therefore, our methodology focuses heavily on the structural and operational mechanics of the funds themselves. Key evaluation criteria include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Expense Ratios and Fee Waivers:</strong> We prioritize funds with the lowest long-term expense ratios, while also factoring in temporary fee waivers that benefit early investors.</li>
        <li><strong>Liquidity and Trading Volume:</strong> High average daily trading volume is crucial for minimizing bid-ask spreads, allowing investors to enter and exit positions cost-effectively.</li>
        <li><strong>Tracking Error:</strong> We measure how closely the ETF's daily NAV changes match the actual price movements of Bitcoin, penalizing funds with significant deviations.</li>
        <li><strong>Custodial Security:</strong> The integrity of the underlying asset is paramount. We review the institutional custodians utilized by the funds, favoring those with proven track records in digital asset security and cold storage solutions.</li>
        <li><strong>AUM (Assets Under Management):</strong> Larger funds generally offer better stability and are less likely to face closure, providing peace of mind for long-term holders.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This systematic approach ensures that our rankings highlight the most robust and investor-friendly vehicles for gaining exposure to the digital asset market.</p>
    </section>

