      <details>
        <summary>What is a Bitcoin ETF?</summary>
        <p>A Bitcoin ETF is an exchange-traded fund that tracks the price of Bitcoin, allowing investors to gain exposure to the cryptocurrency through traditional stock markets without directly holding the digital asset.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Are Bitcoin ETFs safe?</summary>
        <p>While the ETF structure itself is highly regulated and provides institutional custody, the underlying asset (Bitcoin) remains highly volatile and carries significant market risk.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do Bitcoin ETF fees work?</summary>
        <p>Bitcoin ETFs charge a management fee (expense ratio), typically ranging from 0.20% to 1.50%, which is automatically deducted from the fund's assets on an ongoing basis.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I hold a Bitcoin ETF in my retirement account?</summary>
